 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "ARCHITECTURAL TRANSITION: The DAEMON-WRITE epic completes a transition from dual-truth-source (edn files + store.bin cache) to single-truth-source (daemon in-memory state) architecture. This is not a bug fix — it's a phase transition in the system's consistency model. BEFORE: Every process loads its own Store from store.bin, computes independently, flushes independently. Consistency depends on defensive checks (has_new_external_txns, fingerprint comparison) that have proven brittle. The system is eventually consistent with unbounded staleness windows. AFTER: The daemon holds the single authoritative Store. CLI processes are stateless clients. store.bin is a recovery checkpoint, not a shared cache. Consistency is guaranteed by the single-writer property (only the daemon writes store.bin). The system is strongly consistent for all daemon-routed commands. ENABLES: (1) Incremental computation — daemon updates F(S), M(t), R(t) incrementally on each write_tx instead of recomputing from scratch. Path to sub-100ms status. (2) Event-driven guidance — daemon pushes alerts when F(S) drops, hypotheses falsified, conflicts detected. Not just reactive (agent asks) but proactive (system alerts). (3) Access control — daemon can enforce per-agent write namespaces, rate limits, and audit logging. Currently every process has full store access. (4) Cognitive loop — daemon investigates between requests (CE-COGNITION task). Autonomous structural discovery. The DAEMON-WRITE epic is the PREREQUISITE for all of these. Without it, the daemon is a partial optimization that agents bypass for most commands. With it, the daemon IS the store."
